            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">A breadcrumb trail shows the user's current position within a page hierarchy and provides quick navigation back to parent pages.</p>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
                <h3 id="when-to-use-details" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                  When to use
                </h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">To show a user's position within a multi-level hierarchy (e.g. settings, category pages, admin dashboards).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">When users need a reliable way to navigate back to parent pages without the browser back button.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">In deep navigation trees with 3 or more levels.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
                <h3 id="when-not-to-use" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                  When NOT to use
                </h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For flat, single-level navigation &#8212; a back link or tab bar is more appropriate.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">When the path has only one level above the current page &#8212; a back link is sufficient.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">As a primary navigation mechanism; breadcrumbs are supplementary wayfinding.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

