          <!-- Alignment & Placement -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="alignment-placement" class="doc-section-title">Alignment &amp; Placement</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Consistent placement makes breadcrumbs predictable and easy to find.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Page Headers:</strong> Place breadcrumbs above the page title within the page header area, left-aligned.</li>
              <li><strong>Admin Dashboards:</strong> Position below the top navigation bar and above content area for consistent context.</li>
              <li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Consider collapsing to show only the parent and current page, using overflow for deeper paths.</li>
              <li><strong>Settings Pages:</strong> Place at the top of the content panel to show the full settings hierarchy path.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

