          <!-- Complete Do's and Don'ts -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure breadcrumbs are effective, scalable, and accessible.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Reflect true hierarchy:</strong> The trail must mirror the actual page structure, not user click history.</li>
                  <li><strong>Use overflow for deep paths:</strong> Enable <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Overflow=True</code> for 4+ level paths in space-constrained layouts.</li>
                  <li><strong>Show home icon at root:</strong> Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Show Home Icon=ON</code> for the first item when it represents the app root.</li>
                  <li><strong>Use RTL variant for RTL locales:</strong> Apply the RTL variant for Arabic, Hebrew, and other RTL languages.</li>
                  <li><strong>Keep labels concise:</strong> Use short, recognizable page titles (1-3 words) for each breadcrumb item.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Don't show click history:</strong> Breadcrumbs represent structure, not navigation history.</li>
                  <li><strong>Don't bold intermediates:</strong> Only the Current (last) item should be bold and non-interactive.</li>
                  <li><strong>Don't truncate mid-word:</strong> Avoid clipping labels with &#8230; mid-word. Abbreviate the label instead.</li>
                  <li><strong>Don't place home icon everywhere:</strong> The home icon belongs only on the first item.</li>
                  <li><strong>Don't manually mirror for RTL:</strong> Use the RTL variant; don't apply CSS transforms to an LTR breadcrumb.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

